How many degrees are in the smaller angle formed by the minute and hour hands on a clock at 12:30?

    \includegraphics[scale=0.2]{images/blank_clock.jpg}

\textbf{Answer:} At 12:30, the hour hand should be half way between the 12 and the 1.  This means it has moved 1/24th of a rotation clockwise. 1/24th of 360$^{\circ}$ is 15$^{\circ}$. The second hand will be pointing straight down at the 6. This is 180$^{\circ}$ away from the 12, but let us recall that the hour hand has moved 15$^{\circ}$ away from the 12 (towards the 6). So the smaller angle will be $180^{\circ} - 15^{\circ} = \boxed{165^{\circ}}$.
